<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   NUB Issues Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NUB Issues Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0305094594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0905 GMT 3 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0305094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Unification Board [NUB] urged North 
Korea today to earnestly abide by the Armistice Agreement and 
normalize the Military Armistice Commission [MAC] as soon as 
possible. 
  Through a spokesman's statement, the NUB pointed out that 
North Korea's suspension of the MAC function and demand for 
replacing the Armistice Agreement with a peace agreement with 
the United States is a violation of Article 61 of the Armistice 
Agreement, which states that the agreement can only be amended 
upon mutual agreement between North and South Korea, and Article 
5 of the basic agreement between the South and the North. 
  The NUB stressed that until an alternative replacing the 
current armistice organization is provided, the agreements 
should be earnestly abided by and any action intended to make 
the current armistice organization defunct cannot be justified. 
  The NUB pointed out that, at a time when the North Korean 
nuclear issue is at a critical point, North Korea's threatening 
of the current armistice system is intended to delay the 
resolution of the nuclear issue and blur the essence of the 
issue, and strongly urged North Korea to show a sincere attitude 
toward the resolution of the nuclear issue as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

