<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Said To Strengthen Vigilance at PRC Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North Said To Strengthen Vigilance at PRC Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0205135994 Seoul KBS-1 Television Network in Korean 1206 
GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0205135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Diplomatic sources in Beijing reported on 2 May that 
North Korea recently drastically strengthened vigilance at the 
border area with China to prevent North Korean people from 
escaping, and that it instructed the military and police that if 
escapees are discovered, they are to be immediately shot to 
death. 
  The North Korean authorities moved the agents of the 
(?Security Department) and Ministry of Public Security, who were 
serving in the rear, toward the border area of North Hamgyong 
Province and Chagang Province. They are intensely watching over 
the moves of the residents and soldiers. It was learned that 
because of such vigilance, the number of North Koreans escaping 
to China has decreased drastically. 

</TEXT>

