<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Stops GSP Treatment for ROK Fabric Products </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Stops GSP Treatment for ROK Fabric Products </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2804125994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0818 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 28 (YONHAP) -- The European Union [EU] 
virtually finalized a decision to halt generalized system of 
preference (GSP) treatment for South Korean fabric goods from 
July 1 until Seoul withdraws its adjustment tariff on foreign 
products, the Foreign Ministry said Thursday. Industry 
officials predicted that South Korea stands to lose about 2.6 
million dollars worth of exports to Europe due to the EU measure. 
  The decision, apparently in retaliation for Seoul's 
introduction of an adjustment tariff, needs further approval by 
the EU council before going into effect but this is almost 
certain, the ministry said. 
  The EU commission said April 20 that GSP status had been 
suspended for all South Korean products covered under the 
multi-fiber arrangement (MFA). 
  In January, Seoul introduced a 19-percent adjustment tariff 
on fabric imports for 1994 to minimize the impact on local firms 
caused by an unexpected inflow of foreign products. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

