<H3> <TI>   Aviation Agreement Signed With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aviation Agreement Signed With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3004113194 Seoul YONHAP in English 1045 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3004113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 30 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and Russia 
have initiated a new aviation agreement superseding the existing 
one, the Foreign Ministry announced over the weekend. The pact, 
resulting from the bilateral talks held here Thursday and 
Friday, stipulates for a reduced scope of matters for 
negotiations between airlines and new airport fees. 
  Deputy Foreign Minister for Trade Affairs Kim Kwang-tong 
initiated the pact for Korea and acting Aviation Director 
Tumanov of the Transportation Ministry for Russia. The 
agreement will be formally concluded after the two countries 
take necessary steps. The two countries have also agreed to 
proceed with government- and private-level negotiations about 
air routes between them, including the trans-Siberian routes. 

</TEXT>

