<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hyundai, Russian Joint Venture To Build Aircraft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hyundai, Russian Joint Venture To Build Aircraft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2704075994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0607 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704075994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 27 (YONHAP) -- The Hyundai Group will 
manufacture and sell aircraft in a joint venture with Russia's 
Yak Co., a group spokesman said Wednesday. The group's 
affiliate, Hyundai Technology and Development Co., will hold 51 
percent of the joint venture and Yak the remaining 49 percent. 
Company Chairman Chong Mong-ku will be the owner, the spokesman 
said. 
  Hyundai-Yak is to manufacture the Russian aerospace firm's 
150-passenger Yak 42h as well as the short-haul Yak 40h. The 
group's Sosan, Kwangyang and Changwon industrial plants will 
serve as manufacturing sites. The two companies signed a 
contract in November last year, with Yak offering the design and 
manufacturing technology and Hyundai taking care of sales, 
financing and production. Hyundai will dispatch engineers to 
oversee the technology transfer and plans to set up a branch in 
Moscow. 

</TEXT>

