<H3> <TI>   Government To Open Consulate General in Qingdao </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Open Consulate General in Qingdao </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2804023194 Seoul THE KOREA HERALD in English 28 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804023194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA HERALD </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] South Korea will set up a consulate general in the 
Chinese port city of Qingdao by the end of September this year 
at the latest, a Foreign Ministry official said yesterday. He 
said two officials at the ministry will be sent to Qingdao in 
mid-May for preparatory works, which will take three of four 
months. 
  In addition to dealing with usual consular affairs, the new 
consulate general will support Korean companies engaged in 
business in Shandong Province surrounding Qingdao, said the 
official. He added more Korean firms have advanced into 
Shandong than any other Chinese province. 
  Seoul, which formalized diplomatic ties with Beijing in 
August 1991, now has one consulate general in Shanghai. The 
official said the government will push to set up several more 
consulates general in other key cities in China. 

</TEXT>

