<H3> <TI>   U.S. Urges Tokyo To Adopt Stimulus Package </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Urges Tokyo To Adopt Stimulus Package </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0305143894 Tokyo KYODO in English 1431 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0305143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, May 3 KYODO -- U.S. Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher urged Japan to work out a domestic demand 
stimulus package by July's Naples summit of leaders of the 
world's seven major economic powers, Japanese officials said. 
Christopher made the demand during a 35-minute meeting with 
Japanese Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa in Cairo. 
  Kakizawa told Christopher that Japan's new cabinet of Prime 
Minister Tsutomu Hata will make sincere efforts to settle the 
long-standing trade row between Japan and the United States, the 
officials said. 

</TEXT>

