<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia will explore the possibility of making 
contact with Amnesty International, an international 
nongovernmental organization, to discuss various matters, 
especially the East Timor issue, to enable them to understand 
the incorporation of the territory into Indonesia. Foreign 
Minister Ali Alatas said this in Jakarta today before leaving 
for a tripartite meeting with UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali 
and Portuguese Foreign Minister Durao Barroso in Geneva on 6 
May. According to Ali Alatas, Indonesia's readiness to accept 
members of international nongovernmental organizations and 
foreign reporters is part of its effort to create mutual trust 
with Portugal. 
  Regarding Vietnamese refugees on Galang Island, Riau, Ali 
Alatas confirmed that a refugee died from self-immolation when 
an interdepartmental team visited the area recently. Ali Alatas 
deeply regretted the inevitable incident. 

