<F P=103> BK3004095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Indonesian Government will not force Vietnamese 
refugees currently housed on Galang Island in Riau to return 
home. The planned repatriation of all the Vietnamese refugees is 
based on an old agreement between the two countries. Vietnamese 
President Le Duc Anh, who visited Indonesia recently, agreed to 
speed up the repatriation. 
  Replying to reporters on the refugee protests on Galang 
Island where some have died from self-immolation, Foreign 
Minister Ali Alatas said the protests had been staged by a group 
of refugees who failed to pass the screening test for 
resettlement in third countries. The protests were not directed 
at the Indonesian Government but rather at the United Nations 
High Commission for Refugees. According to Ali Alatas, about 
140 out of the estimated 8,000 refugees are prepared to return 
to Vietnam. 

