<H3> <TI>   Government Disapproves of New Pro-Democracy Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Disapproves of New Pro-Democracy Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405105294 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0700 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government does not recognize the existence of 
the Association of Democratic People [PRD] established on 2 May. 
This is because the organization is inclined to conduct 
political activities and is therefore against Law No. 3/1985 on 
political parties and the functional group. Speaking after 
chairing a coordinated meeting in Jakarta, Coordinating Minister 
for Politics and Security Affairs Susilo Sudarman said the three 
organizations legally allowed to conduct political activities 
are the United Development Party, the Functional Group, and the 
Indonesian Democratic Party. Therefore, the existence of PRD is 
against the above law. 

