<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRG Economic Delegation Visits Vientiane </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRG Economic Delegation Visits Vientiane </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives, Meets Khamphoui </H4>

<F P=102> BK0405065194 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405065194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday in Vientiane capital, Khamphoui 
Keoboualapha, deputy prime minister of the Lao People's 
Democratic Republic [LPDR] and chairman of the Committee for 
Planning and Cooperation, received a courtesy call from the 
economic cooperation and development delegation of the Federal 
Republic of Germany [FRG] headed by Wighard Hardte, state 
secretary and deputy minister for economic cooperation and 
development, which is paying a visit to the LPDR. During the 
call, the host and guests conversed in an atmosphere of 
intimacy. Deputy Prime Minister Khamphoui Keoboualapha hailed 
and highly assessed the visit to Laos by the delegation, 
pointing out that it served to further strengthen the relations 
of friendship between the LPDR and the FRG. He wished the 
delegation success during its visit. 
  The FRG economic cooperation and development delegation 
arrived in Vientiane at noon on the same day for a three-day 
visit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

