<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRG Economic Delegation Visits Vientiane </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRG Economic Delegation Visits Vientiane </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Signs Agreement, Concludes Visit </H4>

<F P=102> BK0405063094 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405063094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A ceremony was held at Lan Xang Hotel on 3 May to 
sign an agreement on 1993 financial cooperation for 
implementation in 1994 between the Government of the Lao 
People's Democratic Republic and the Government of the Federal 
Republic of Germany. Mrs. Khampheng Phonsena, vice chairman of 
the Committee for Planning and Cooperation, represented the Lao 
Government at the signing ceremony, while the German side was 
represented by Wighard Hardte, state secretary and deputy 
minister for economic cooperation and development. Witnessing 
the signing ceremony were Souban Salitthilat, deputy foreign 
affairs minister; Claus Soenksen, ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary of Germany to Laos; and a number of officials 
concerned from both sides. 
  The agreement stipulates that the Government of the Federal 
Republic of Germany will grant financial aid of 23 (?million) 
deutsche marks to Laos for spending in the second stage of the 
rural telecommunications development project, including 
telephone links among provinces and major urban areas throughout 
the country, in addition to the first phase of the project which 
has already been completed. 
  The German economic cooperation and development delegation 
concluded its three-day visit to Laos and left for home at noon 
today. 

</TEXT>

