<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Short Wave Radio Contract Signed With Australia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Short Wave Radio Contract Signed With Australia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405031294 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405031294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A ceremony was held at Lan Xang Hotel on the 
evening of 29 April to sign a contract to buy a 50-kw short wave 
radio broadcasting system between the Ministry of Information 
and Culture and the Telstra Company of Australia. Representing 
the Lao side at the signing ceremony was Bounteng Vongsai, 
deputy minister of information and culture; while the Australian 
side was represented by Barley, Telstra Lao branch director. 
Witnessing the contract signing were Bouasi Chaleunsouk, deputy 
minister of information and culture; Michael Mann, ambassador 
extraordinary and plenipotentiary of Australia to Laos; 
representatives of the Ministries of Foreign Affairs and 
Finance; and senior officials from various services concerned. 
  The aim of purchasing the 50-kw short wave radio 
broadcasting 
system at a cost of more than $1 million is to allow all 
localities and provinces throughout the country to receive 
broadcasting programs of the national radio station. This is 
because at present, many regions in the country are still unable 
to tune in the station's programs. Installation of the system 
will enable our country to possess a new modern short wave radio 
broadcasting station to beam radio programs to all regions 
throughout the country. Installation of this new radio 
transmitter will be completed within one year beginning on the 
day the contract was signed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

