<DATE1>  3 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Authorities' Treatment of Koreans Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese Authorities' Treatment of Koreans Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Chongnyon `Suppression' Denounced </H4>

<F P=102> SK0305114194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1055 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0305114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 1 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- An 
Osaka prefectural meeting of Koreans in Japan was held at the 
Nakaosaka Korean Primary and Middle School on April 30 to 
denounce the suppression of the Osaka Organisation of the 
General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) by 
the Japanese authorities. 
  A statement of the spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the 
DPRK was read out and O Hyong-chin, vice-chairman of the Central 
Standing Committee of Chongnyon and chairman of the Osaka 
prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon, made a report at the 
meeting attended by more than 3,000 Chongnyon officials and 
Korean residents in Japan. 
  The reporter pungently denounced the large-scale suppression 
unprecedented in history by the Japanese police, branding the 
case as a grave hostile act against the DPRK and as an 
unjustifiable political suppression of Koreans in Japan and 
Chongnyon. 
  Japanese figures including the vice-chairman of the Osaka 
headquarters of the Japan Social-Democratic Party and a lawyer 
made solidarity speeches, which were followed by indignation 
speeches of representatives of Chongnyon and the Democratic 
Union of Korean Women in Japan. 
  The meeting adopted a resolution and elected delegates who 
would conduct a protest action against the Osaka Precfectural 
Police and the Higashi Police Station. 
  In connection with the outrages by the Osaka Prefectural 
Police, Ho Chong-man, chief vice-chairman of the Central 
Standing Committee of Chongnyon, and Kim Tae-hui, director of 
the International Department of the Chongnyon Central Standing 
Committee, on April 28 visited the headquarters of the Liberal 
Democratic Party and met the chairman of the Policy Affairs 
Research Council and deputy secretary-general of the party and 
handed them a request of the Chongnyon Central Standing 
Committee addressed to its President Yohei Kono. 
  On April 26, delegates of the Chongnyon Central Standing 
Committee visited the headquarters of the Komei Party to hand it 
a request addressed to its Chairman Koshi Ishida. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-51857 </DOCNO>
