<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Authorities' Treatment of Koreans Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese Authorities' Treatment of Koreans Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Grave Consequences' Discussed </H4>

<F P=102> SK0305113994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1100 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0305113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 3 (KCNA) -- The Japanese 
reactionaries must ponder over the grave consequences arising 
from their unreasonable acts, stop the repression of the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and the 
Korean nationals in Japan and apologise for it, declares MINJU 
CHOSON today. 
  The news analyst says: 
  A sequence of savage repression by the Japanese 
reactionaries 
such as search of the hall of the Osaka prefectural headquarters 
of Chongnyon and its branch offices and the houses of senior 
officials is a heinous hostile act to wantonly infringe on the 
democratic rights of Koreans in Japan and stifle Chongnyon and 
an intolerable provocation against the DPRK. 
  Their repressive acts hitherto against Chongnyon and Koreans 
in Japan are countless, but there had been no such wholesale 
search and rampage as the recent one. This clearly shows their 
anti-Chongnyon, anti-DPRK campaign has reached a very grave 
stage. 
  Chongnyon is a dignified and authoritative organisation of 
overseas citizens of the DPRK which is engaged in righteous 
activities to defend the democratic national rights of Koreans 
in Japan, achieve the reunification of the country and promote 
friendship with the Japanese people. Therefore, there is no 
ground for Chongnyon to be the target of repression. 
  It is unpardonable for the Japanese authorities to join the 
United States and the South Korean puppets in the row over the 
"nuclear issue" of the DPRK and deliberately aggravate the 
situation, while resorting to vicious anti-DPRK, anti-Chongnyon 
acts. 
  Their reckless acts are aimed at blocking the legitimate 
activities of Chongnyon, controlling and restricting the life of 
Koreans in Japan and impairing the just peace policy of the DPRK 
at any cost. 
  However, it will bring into relief their inferiority and 
ferocity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

