<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Publishing House Marked in Tokyo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of Publishing House Marked in Tokyo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0305113594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1033 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0305113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 1 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- A 
meeting was held in Tokyo on April 30 to commemorate the 40th 
anniversary of the founding of the Kuwol Sobang Publishing House. 
  Ho Chong-man, chief vice-chairman of the Central Standing 
Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon), in his speech said that the 40-year-long path 
traversed by the Kuwol Sobang Publishing House was the course of 
loyalty and patriotism along which the publishing house, with 
the edition, publication and dissemination of the press of 
chuche-type, firmly armed the officials of Chongnyon and Koreans 
in Japan with the revolutionary ideas of the great leader 
Generalissimo Kim Il-song and the dear leader Marshal Kim 
Chong-il, propagandized within and without the immortal chuche 
idea and the socialist homeland of chuche and greatly 
contributed to national reunification and the patriotic work of 
Chongnyon. 
  Kim Won-taek, director of the publishing house, in his 
report 
said that workers of the publishing house would make all their 
efforts to fulfil their heavy duty as a standard-bearer of the 
struggle for the development of the movement of Koreans in Japan 
in depth and a guide in the ideological education work of 
Chongnyon under the uplifted banner of the great chuche idea in 
response to the teachings of the great leader. 
  The meeting adopted a letter to Marshal Kim Chong-il. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

