<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Campaigns for 10-Point Program Held Abroad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Campaigns for 10-Point Program Held Abroad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0205104394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1021 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0205104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Signature campaigns have 
been conducted in Peru and Jamaica in support of the "10-point 
Programme of the Great Unity of the Whole Nation for the 
Reunification of the Country" put forward by the great leader 
President Kim Il-song. 
  The signature campaign which began in Peru on April 6 
according to a call of the Peruvian Initiative Committee of the 
Signature Campaign for supporting the "10-point Programme of the 
Great Unity of the Whole Nation for the Reunification of the 
Country" involved the president and the general secretary of the 
National Executive Committee of the Left Revolutionary Union of 
Peru, the chairman and the organisational secretary of the 
People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, the 
general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist 
Party of Peru (Red Motherland), the general secretary of the 
Socialist Revolutionary Party of Peru, the general secretary of 
the Socialist Party of Peru, the chairman of the Peruvian Front 
for National Liberation, the general secretary of the Central 
Committee of the Peruvian Communist Party, the general secretary 
of the General Confederation of Peasants of Peru, and other 
political and public figures and broad segments of people. 
  More than 2.75 million people had participated in the 
signature campaign as of April 20. 
  In Kingston, Jamaica, participants in a meeting which was 
held in celebration of April 15 conducted a signature campaign 
on April 16. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

