<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indian Official Interviewed on Korean Army Day </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Indian Official Interviewed on Korean Army Day </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0205215594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1503 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0205215594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Under the wise guidance 
of the great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il, the Korean people and People's Army are 
defending the sovereignty of the country and the gains of 
socialism with honour, smashing the war manoeuvres of the 
imperialists and [words indistinct] general secretary of the 
Democratic Youth Federation of India, in an interview with the 
KCNA reporter in India on April 18 on the occasion of the 62nd 
founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army. 
  The general secretary said Comrade Kim Chong-il possessed of 
rare wisdom and outstanding ability of leadership, has not only 
built an invincible anthropocentric socialism based on the 
singlehearted unity of the leader, the party and the masses but 
also put forward unique idea and theory of Army building and 
consolidated the defences of the country as firm as rock. 
  The secret of the victory won by the Korean people and 
People's Army at every step in the decisive battle with U.S. 
imperialism and its allied force in recent years lies in the 
outstanding leadership of Comrade Kim Chong-il, supreme 
commander of the Korean People's Army, who is possessed of iron 
will and matchless grit, he emphasized. 
  Saying that the acute situation created on the Korean 
peninsula is entirly attributable to the reckless military 
adventures and interference of the United States, he demanded 
that the U.S. withdraw its forces from South Korea, discontinue 
all forms of war rehearsals and stop the deployment of Patriot 
missiles in South Korea at once. 

</TEXT>

