<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Book Published in Foreign Languages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Book Published in Foreign Languages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0305113494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1028 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0305113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 3 (KCNA) -- The foreign languages 
publishing house brought out the book "President Kim Il-song" in 
foreign languages. 
  Carried in it are the impressions of well-known political 
and 
public figures of Japan who had the audience of the great leader 
President Kim Il-song while visiting Korea. 
  The book contains a part of the two-volume "President Kim 
Il-song" which was presented to him as a gift on his 80th 
birthday on April 15, 1992. 
  Carried on the first page of the book is a photograph of the 
great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  The book gives more than 40 articles including "The Most 
Distinguished People's Leader" by Tomomi Narita, ex-chairman of 
the Japan Socialist Party, "The Man Who Moves Asia and the 
World" by Takeo Takagi, ex-director of the Society for 
Japan-Korea Cultural Exchange and editorial writer of YOMIURI 
SHIMBUN, and "The Korean People Who Receive the Guidance of 
Great President Kim Il-song is Really Happy" by Tsunehiko 
Antaku, former member of the House of Representatives. 

</TEXT>

