<H3> <TI>   More Reports on Kim Il-song Birthday Activities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Reports on Kim Il-song Birthday Activities </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Nations Commemorate Birthday </H4>

<F P=102> SK0405110494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1009 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- The birthday of the great 
leader President Kim Il-song was celebrated in different 
countries. 
  Cultural evenings were held in Dar es Salaam of Tanzania and 
by the Left Revolutionary Union of Peru. 
  Speaking at the cultural evening, Angel Castro Lavarello, 
president of the National Executive Committee of the union, said: 
  "The great leader Generalissimo Kim Il-song is the sun of 
the 
Korean nation with a 5,000-year history. 
  "He is the great leader who founded the chuche idea and has 
devoted his whole life to the national liberation and human 
emancipation. 
  "He is the ever-victorious, iron-willed brilliant commander, 
standard-bearer of the world revolution and veteran of 
revolution and construction who defeated two imperialisms in one 
generation and brought a new era of independence against 
imperialism." 
  DPRK film shows and photo exhibitions, lecture meetings, 
book 
exhibitions and other functions to celebrate April 15 were 
organised in Denmark, Malta, Mozambique and by the maritime 
regional Russia- Korea Friendship Association, the Zimbabwean 
National Liberation War Veterans Committee, the Belgian 
International Solidarity Centre, the guard unit of the Angolan 
president, the Senegalese Socialist Party, the Zimbabwe-Korea 
Solidarity and Friendship Association, the National Committee of 
the National Movement of the Genuine Lumumbist Combatants of 
Zaire, the Cairo film centre of Egypt, the Yara cinema house in 
Havana, Cuba, the Sandinist Centre of workers of Nicaragua, the 
Imazic company of Algeria, in Zashikan County of Ghana, at the 
Chollima Institute of Agricultural Science of Tanzania and in 
Sancti Spiritus Province of Cuba. 

</TEXT>

