<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Chong-il Receives Messages From Abroad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3004044694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0420 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3004044694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 30 (KCNA) -- Solidarity messages 
came to the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il from foreign party 
leaders supporting the Korean people's struggle to defend the 
dignity of their nation and the sovereignty of their country. 
  Boris Petkov, chairman of the Executive Council of the 
Central Committee of the Bulgarian Communist Party (Marxists), 
in his message said the Bulgarian communists resolutely 
denounced the United States and the South Korean authorities for 
hourly increasing the danger of war on the Korean peninsula, and 
urged a halt to military pressure and all hostile acts against 
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  The Bulgarian communists will invariably stand firm on the 
side of the Korean people who are waging an indomitable struggle 
for justice and peace and for the triumphant advance of the 
socialist cause, he stressed. 
  Dragomir Draskovic, president of the National Committee of 
the League of Communists-Movement for Yugoslavia, Ali Hassan, 
general secretary of the Supreme Council of the Nationalist 
Socialist Party of Syria in Lebanon, and Guzman Rivera 
Castaneda, general secretary of the Socialist Revolutionary 
Party of Peru, in their messages expressed the belief that the 
Korean people under the wise leadership of Comrade Kim Chong-il 
would win a great victory in their struggle to accomplish the 
cause of building socialism of chuche and defend the security of 
their country. They stressed that they would stand for ever by 
the Workers' Party and People of Korea who are fighting the 
United States and its followers. 

</TEXT>

