<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Kim Chong-il's Work Commemorated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of Kim Chong-il's Work Commemorated </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0305113294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1012 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0305113294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 3 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held at the 
People's Palace of Culture Monday to mark the tenth anniversary 
of the publication of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il's 
famous work "On Further Improving the Work of the Trade Unions" 
(May 3, 1984). 
  In the work, Comrade Kim Chong-il said the trade unions are 
mass political organisations of the working class and dependable 
assistants and defenders of the party. And he gave scientific 
and perfect answers to all theoretical and practical questions 
in the building and activity of trade unions ranging from the 
character and mission of the trade unions to their fighting goal 
and tasks, principles and ways of activity. 
  In his report at the meeting, Chu Song-il, chairman of the 
Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of 
Korea, praised Comrade Kim Chong-il's work as a unique and 
revolutionary, great charter of the trade union movement in that 
it consummated the theory of building the trade unions and their 
activities in the present time and developed them to completion. 
  "In the period following the publication of the work", he 
said, "The work for imbuing the trade unions with the great 
chuche idea has been invigorated under the wise guidance of the 
party with the result that the unions have successfully 
fulfilled their duties and tasks as organisations of ideological 
education and active assistants of the Workers' Party of Korea." 
  "We are faced with the honorable task to defend socialism 
from all challenges and obstructive moves of the imperialists 
and reactionaries, exalt it and accomplish the cause of national 
reunification at an early date. The unionists must devotedly 
work to defend and exalt our socialism, that is, our life and 
soul," stressed the reporter. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

