<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Article Views Kim Chong-il `Historical Letter' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Article Views Kim Chong-il `Historical Letter' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405110594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1041 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- The idea, theory and 
policies set forth by the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il in 
his historical letter "On Further Improving the Work of the 
Trade Unions" have displayed their great vitality in practice 
and their validity and attraction have been fully proven, says 
NODONG SINMUN today in a signed article devoted to the tenth 
anniversary of the publication of the letter. 
  In his work Comrade Kim Chong-il set forth the highly 
important tasks to build, strengthen and develop the trade 
unions including the tasks to push ahead with the three 
revolutions, ideological, technical and cultural, further 
enhance the role of trade union organizations in the socialist 
construction, firmly build up the trade union ranks and enhance 
the militant function of the trade union organizations. 
  Referring to the validity and vitality of the work, the 
article says: 
  They are evidently manifested in the fact that continued 
innovations and upswing are being effected in the socialist 
construction because, with the three revolutions successfully 
carried out, the Korean working class has been well prepared as 
faithful ranks which hold in esteem the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il in one mind of loyalty and filial piety, and the 
leading and vanguard role of the working class has been enhanced. 
  Technical and cultural revolutions, along with the 
ideological revolution, have been pushed ahead among the working 
class and trade union members. As a result, their technical and 
cultural standard is constantly increasing and their sense of 
duty and role in carrying out the technical revolution is 
growing more and more. 
  With the promotion of creative cooperation between workers 
and scientists and technicians, scientific and technical 
problems arising in putting the national economy on a 
chuche-oriented, modernized and scientific basis have been 
satisfactorily solved. Thus, the chuche character and 
independence of our industry have been consistently strengthened 
and production is going up at a fast speed. 
  Through the efforts to implement the idea and theory and 
policies set forth in the work, the party's economic policy 
propaganda and economic agitation have been activated and 
various forms of mass movements and socialist emulation drives 
have been dynamically conducted by the trade union organizations 
to powerfully encourage the working class and union members to 
the socialist economic construction. 
  In the flame of the socialist emulation drives our working 
class and trade union members made big innovative achievements 
in the fulfilment of the third seven-year plan and successfully 
carried out large-scale projects for the everlasting prosperity 
of the country. 
  The validity and vitality are also expressed in that the 
trade union ranks have been firmly built up and their militant 
function and role enhanced considerably, the article says. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

