<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plan `Overfulfilled' in Various Economic Areas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Plan `Overfulfilled' in Various Economic Areas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0105082694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0810 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0105082694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 1 (KCNA) -- The April plan has been 
overfulfilled in different sectors of the national economy in 
Korea. 
  The Korea general silk corporation fulfilled its monthly 
production plan by April 29. Notably, the export silk garment 
factory under the corporation fulfilled its plan for the first 
half of the year at 107.5 percent till April 14. 
  The Pyongyang silk-reeling mill, the Anju silk mill and the 
Sinuiju textile mill carried out their monthly assignments 
respectively at 115, 110 and 102 percent. 
  The general bureau of salt industry fulfilled the monthly 
industrial output value at 112.5 percent and salt production at 
101 percent as of April 26. 
  Monthly coal and mineral production plans were overfulfilled 
at many coal and ore mines including the Nipsok and Taehyang 
coal mines and the Songsan and Songchon ore mines. 
  Power stations across the country including the East 
Pyongyang thermal power station and the Kanggye youth power 
station also fulfilled their monthly electrical power production 
plan. 

</TEXT>

