<H3> <TI>   Livestock Breeders Hold National Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Livestock Breeders Hold National Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3004045094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0431 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3004045094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 30 (KCNA) - A national meeting of 
active stockbreeders was held in Pyongyang over April 28-29. 
  Attending the meeting were Politburo member of the C.C. 
[Central Committee], the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and 
Premier of the Administration Council Kang Song-san, Secretary 
of the C.C., the WPK So Kwan-hi and Vice-Premier Kim Chang-chu. 
  The meeting reviewed the achievements and experiences 
registered in past years in implementing the party's policy of 
stockbreeding and discussed measures to make a new progress in 
livestock production in conformity with the demand of the 
party's revolutionary economic strategy. 
  The meeting dealt with matters of consolidating the material 
and technical foundations of stockbreeding, raising more 
domestic animals at workteams and families, placing 
stockbreeding on a scientific and technical basis and improving 
veterinary and anti- epizootic work, so as to boost the output 
of meat and eggs. 
  A letter of pledge to the great leader President Kim Il-song 
and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il was adopted at the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

