<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Writers Urged To Participate in Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Writers Urged To Participate in Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2704231594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1501 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2704231594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 27 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
Central Committee of the General Federation of the Unions of 
Literature and Arts of Korea called upon all the literary and 
art organizations, patriotic writers and artists in South Korea 
and abroad aspiring after national independence and 
reunification of the country to make a bold decision to 
participate in a national conference and actively lead other 
political parties, organizations and individual figures to join 
them. 
  In a statement today the spokesman said the Kim Yong-sam 
group's opposition to the proposal of a national conference 
initiated by a joint meeting of the DPRK Government, political 
parties and public organizations is, in essence, intended to 
conceal their flunkeyist, treacherous nature and monopolize 
North-South dialogue. 
  "The South Korean authorities claiming to be 'civilian' have 
blocked all dialogues and contacts between political parties, 
organizations and individual personages," the spokesman said, 
adding: "This clearly shows that they do not want national 
reconciliation and unity but seek to prolong their remaining 
days as henchmen of outside forces." 

</TEXT>

