<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KPA Soldiers Complete Tideland Reclamation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KPA Soldiers Complete Tideland Reclamation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2804152094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1507 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 28 (KCNA) -- Kumsong tideland 
reclamation, one more creation of eternal value, has been 
successfully completed in Korea by People's Army [KPA] soldiers 
mobilized in peaceful construction and builders. 
  A great nature-remaking project for damming up a wide sea 
extending scores of ri along the West Coast from Kwangnyang Bay 
to Kumsong-ri in Onchon County, South Pyongan Province, has been 
completed to obtain 3,300 hectares of arable land. 
  Hundreds of hectares of paddy fields have already been 
adjusted as a standardized field like a checker board, 
irrigation and drainage waterways to prevent damages from 
drought, flood and brine forever and roads extending tens of 
kilometres have been built. 
  Paddy fields have been divided into fields of 25 hectares 
each. This year will witness the first farming in these fields. 
  A ceremony for the completion of the Kumsong tideland 
reclamation took place on the spot on April 27. 
  Vice Marshal Choe Kwang, Politburo member of the Central 
Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and chief of the 
General Staff of the Korean People's Army, conveyed a message 
of thanks of the C.C. [Central Committee], the WPK at the 
ceremony. 
  The message highly estimated the KPA soldiers and builders 
for their indomitable spirit and shining feats performed in the 
large- scale nature-remaking project with the unshakable faith 
that they have nothing impossible under the wise leadership of 
the party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

