<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CPP Expells Two More Top Anti-Sison Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405023994 Manila PHILIPPINE DAILY INQUIRER in English 29 
Apr 94 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405023994 </F>
<F P=104>  Manila PHILIPPINE DAILY INQUIRER </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two more top communist leaders in Mindanao were 
expelled from the underground movement for their refusal to 
recognize Jose Maria Sison as the chair of the Communist Party 
of the Philippines (CPP), reports reaching Camp Aguinaldo said 
yesterday. 
  Col. Angelo Reyes, commanding officer of the Civil Relations 
Service (CRS) of the Armed Forces of the Philippines, said the 
CPP "faces more serious crises" due to the worsening rift within 
the movement." Reyes identified those expelled as Timoteo Pupa, 
Central Mindanao Regional Committee (CMRC) secretary and Ike de 
los Reyes, Pupa's deputy. 

