BFN 

  [Text] Thousands of cassette tapes were destroyed earlier 
today at the Board of Investments' parking lot in Makati. The 
pirated music tapes were confiscated from various establishments 
these past three months. 
  Trade Secretary Rizalino Navarro, General Javier Carbonell 
of 
the Videogram Regulatory Board, and representatives from the 
music industry witnessed the destruction of the tapes. 
  Millions of pesos are lost from piracy and counterfeiting of 
articles with intellectual property rights including movies and 
videos tapes, medicine, garments, books, and other publications. 

