<H3> <TI>   Photographs Indicate Kim Il-song's Growth Bigger </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Photographs Indicate Kim Il-song's Growth Bigger </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405095794 Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO in Korean 4 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] North Korean President Kim Il-song's lump is 
growing as time goes by. It has been confirmed that President 
Kim Il-song's lump on the back of his neck is growing bigger and 
causes him discomfort. 
  CHUNGANG ILBO has exclusively obtained photographs taken by 
a 
Western figure, who recently visited North Korea, using his 
video recorder. Compared to a photograph that was made public 
in 1988 (black and white), these photographs show that his lump 
is growing bigger (top picture) and expanding toward his head 
(middle picture) and his lower neck (bottom picture). This lump 
is not fatal. President Kim Il-song has been undergoing 
acupuncture treatment since the seventies because surgery on 
this lump may hurt his brain. 

</TEXT>

