<H3> <TI>   Students Stage Anti-U.S. Kwangju Demonstration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Students Stage Anti-U.S. Kwangju Demonstration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405053394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0526 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405053394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kwangju, May 4 (YONHAP) -- Some 400 college students 
staged a surprise anti-U.S. demonstration near the American 
Center in this southwestern city at 5:30 A.M. Wednesday, 
declaring that "We oppose the United States creating a war 
atmosphere." 
  The students, members of Namchongnyon, an activist 
organization comprising students from Chonnam National and 
Choson Universities as well as other schools in Kwangju and 
South Cholla Province, tried to storm into the American Center 
but were blocked by riot police firing tear-gas. 
  A clash between the police and students wielding paint 
bottles and rocks ensued, injuring some 10 policemen and 
students who were taken to nearby hospitals for treatment. 
  At 6:10, the students moved to the South Cholla police 
agency 
to demand the release of their arrested fellows, while throwing 
over 20 paint bottles at the agency building. 

</TEXT>

