<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Student Association Inaugurated at Demonstration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Student Association Inaugurated at Demonstration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405123994 Seoul YONHAP in English 1108 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 4 (YONHAP) -- The seventh Sochongnyon or 
the Federation of Seoul Area College Student Associations was 
inaugurated in a rally held at Hongik University in western 
Seoul Wednesday afternoon. 
  About 2,000 activist students from Seoul National University 
and 39 other universities and colleges in the Seoul area 
attended the rally. 
  A student manifesto read at the rally claimed that "the 
government has one-sidedly yielded to market-opening pressures 
from world capitalist countries, causing threat to the very 
survival of workers let alone 10 million farmers." 
  It also asserted that "the United States continues to pose a 
nuclear war threat to North Korea to build up the danger of war 
on the whole area of the Korean peninsula." 
  Yi Chong-uk, a Hanyang University senior, was chosen as new 
Sochongnyon chairman at the rally which also set "resistance to 
rice market opening" and "anti-U.S. struggles" as Sochongnyon's 
major tasks of the year. 
  Prior to the rally, participating students staged a 
demonstration along a 2-km street from the Sinchon intersection 
to the Hongik campus, shouting "no war on the Korean peninsula" 
and "no market opening." 
  Large police forces were mobilized in the Sinchon area but 
no 
clashes were reported during the demonstration. 

</TEXT>

