<H3> <TI>   Kakizawa Criticizes Nagano Remark </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kakizawa Criticizes Nagano Remark </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0505110294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 May 94 
Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0505110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent Hiroki Fukuta] </F>
  [Text] Jerusalem, 4 May -- Commenting on Justice Minister 
Shigeto Nagano's remark that the 1937 Nanjing atrocity [Nankin 
gyakusatsu] is a fabrication, Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa, 
who is visiting Israel, told a group of Japanese correspondents 
on 4 May: "Japan should be engaged in soul-searching over its 
past act of aggression. If the justice minister's remark has 
caused a misunderstanding among Japan's neighboring nations, as 
foreign minister I will work to dispel that misunderstanding." 

</TEXT>

