<H3> <TI>   SDPJ's Uehara Seeks `Grand Union of Doves' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDPJ's Uehara Seeks `Grand Union of Doves' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0405044994 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 1 May 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0405044994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During talks with reporters in Naha city on 30 
April, Kosuke Uehara disclosed that he would seek to establish a 
"grand union of doves" by gathering forces advocating protection 
of the Constitution from Sakigake [Harbinger], the Democratic 
Socialist Party, and a liberal group in the Liberal Democratic 
Party. Uehara is a member of the Social Democratic Party of 
Japan [SDPJ], and former director general of the National Land 
Agency and Hokkaido and Okinawa Development Agency. On the 
formation of a "grand union of doves," Uehara said: "It will 
formulate its policies toward the Japan-U.S. security pact, 
Self-Defense Forces, and foreign affairs based on the agreement 
made when the coalition government was inaugurated." 

</TEXT>

