<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Reports on Sihanouk's Cease-Fire Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Reports on Sihanouk's Cease-Fire Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sihanouk Urges KR To Respond </H4>

<F P=102> BK0305120294 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1100 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0305120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1100 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Message from King Norodom Sihanouk to Khieu Samphan, </F>
chairman of the party of Democratic Kampuchea, dated 3 May -- 
read by announcer] 
  [Text] Excellency, I am honored to inform the party of 
Democratic Kampuchea [PDK] of the following: 
  1. Abiding by the most enthusiastic, unanimous demand of our 
beloved compatriots, in my capacity as the king of the Kingdom 
of Cambodia I would like to urgently beseech the Royal 
Government of Cambodia [RGC] and Khmer Royal Armed Forces [KRAF] 
and the PDK and National Army of Democratic Kampuchea [NADK] to 
immediately accept my formal and solemn proposal for an 
immediate, complete, and unconditional cease-fire and a 
standstill of all current positions of both sides. 
  2. If this cease-fire proposal is already accepted by the 
RGC and KRAF and the PDK and NADK, I invite the RGC and KRAF and 
the PDK and NADK to immediately send me two generals of the KRAF 
and two other generals of the NADK to form, under my 
chairmanship, a cease-fire observation committee to oversee this 
cease-fire throughout the Cambodian territory. 
  3. The roundtable proposal of which your excellency has 
already been aware for the past few days will be held inside the 
royal palace in Phnom Penh or at the Cambodian palace in 
Pyongyang when the cease-fire throughout Cambodia becomes truly 
effective and concretely secure. 
  Prince Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh and Samdech Hun Sen have 
agreed with and given their full support to this proposal since 
the afternoon of Monday, 2 May 1994. Presently, I am confident 
that your excellency will make your answer to my above proposal 
known to me. 
  Affectionately yours, 
  [Signed] Norodom Sihanouk 
  [Dated] Phnom Penh, 3 May 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

