<H3> <TI>   Malaysian Minister Urges Reason in Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Malaysian Minister Urges Reason in Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405110294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1001 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- "The nuclear issue of the 
Korean peninsula must be resolved by means of negotiation, not 
by means of pressure", said the defence minister of Malaysia at 
a press conference. 
  "Malaysia," he went on, "considers that the countries 
concerned should show reason in settling the problem of the 
Korean peninsula and not cause a war. If any party resorts to a 
means of high pressure, a war would break out in that region and 
it would affect the security of the Asia-Pacific region." 
  "Malaysia hopes the countries concerned sit at a negotiating 
table and resolve this issue in a peaceful way and opposes any 
country building up nuclear weapons or increasing nuclear 
capacity," he said. 

</TEXT>

