<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Checking and Frustrating South Korean Puppets' Moves To </F>
Develop Nuclear Weapons Called For" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- Presidium member Chong 
Tu-hwan of the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the 
Reunification of the Fatherland [DFRF] released a press 
statement Wednesday in connection with the fact that the South 
Korean puppets' moves for the development of nuclear weapons 
have reached a dangerous stage. He branded the Kim Yong-sam 
group's moves for the development of nuclear weapons as a gross 
violation of the joint declaration on denuclearisation between 
the North and South, a perfidy and treachery to the nation and a 
heinous challenge to the DPRK's efforts for denuclearisation and 
peace. 
  Recalling the fact that the Wolsong heavy water reactor 
alone 
has produced as much spent nuclear fuel containing plutonium as 
is capable of manufacturing some 370 nuclear shells, he 
continues: 
  "The Kim Yong-sam group is putting spurs to the development 
of nuclear weapons of late. It proves that they have neither 
the idea to take hands with the fellow countrymen, nor the will 
to solve the reunification question of the country in a peaceful 
way. The Kim Yong-sam clique is undisguisedly scheming to 
nullify the North-South joint declaration on denuclearisation, 
openly talking about the `right to possess nuclear weapons.' 
This is motivated by their sinister scheme to justify and 
legalize their development of nuclear weapons. If their moves 
to develop nuclear weapons are not held in check, the whole 
nation cannot escape a nuclear holocaust to be entailed 
therefrom. All people who are concerned about the future 
destiny of the country and the nation, if only a little, must 
turn out in the struggle to check and frustrate the puppets' 
moves to develop nuclear weapons and overthrow the Kim Yong-sam 
group, irrespective of party affiliation, political view and ism 
and ideology. "The Kim Yong-sam group must immediately stop 
developing nuclear weapons to destroy the nation and at once 
step down as unanimously demanded by the South Korean people." 

</TEXT>

