<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Reports on Student Demonstrations in ROK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0505054994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0452 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0505054994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- Over 2,000 students of 40 
universities and colleges in Seoul including Seoul National 
University, Yonsei University and Korea University had the 
inaugural ceremony of the seventh-term Seoul District Federation 
of General Student Councils (Sochongnyon) at Hongik University 
on May 4 and staged a demonstration calling for an objection to 
treacherous rice market opening and U.S. troops' withdrawal, 
according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  They said that the Kim Yong-sam puppet clique yielded to the 
U.S. pressure to open market so the lives of 10 million peasants 
and even workers are being threatened. 
  The students charged that the United States continues to 
threaten the North with a nuclear war and increase the war 
atmosphere on the Korean peninsula. They demanded that 
authorities refuse a "ratification of the final act of the 
Uruguay Round of world trade talks at the National Assembly," 
object to rice import liberalization and realise the U.S. 
troops' pullout and denuclearisation and disarmament and signing 
of peace agreement. 

</TEXT>

