showed up at the Hyonchung shrine [shrine to General Yi Sun-sin] 
in Asan, South Chungchong Province, South Korea, some time ago 
and talked as if he were practising something, succeeding to the 
"patriotism" and "self-sacrificing spirit" of Yi Sun-sin, a 
famous general who performed feats in repulsing Japanese 
aggression at the end of the 16th century. 
  NODONG SINMUN today brands his mishmash as an intolerable 
insult to and a mockery of the patriotic spirit of the 
forerunners. 
