<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-087 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Figures Condemn Chongnyon `Crackdown' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese Figures Condemn Chongnyon `Crackdown' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405110394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1004 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 2 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- Public 
figures of Japan denounced most brutal crackdown on the Osaka 
prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon [General Association of 
Korean Residents in Japan] and its branches by the Japanese 
police. 
  A member of the House of Councillors, Hideo Den, said that 
the police suppression of Koreans in Japan is creating an 
anti-DPRK atmosphere under the pretext of "nuclear suspicion 
against the North" faked up by the United States. "The Japanese 
Government must probe the truth and apologize," he demanded. 
  A lawyer, Shigeru Tokoi, said that the recent search reminds 
one of the crackdown on Koreans in Japan including the 
suppression of national education on the eve of the Korean war. 
  Akira Iwai, chairman of the Japan Committee for Supporting 
the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, said he, as 
a Japanese, cannot tolerate the assault on a Korean girl student 
and unreasonable police search of Chongnyon when the DPRK-USA 
talks had collapsed and the Korean situation had become more 
strained. 
  Yasusaburo Hoshino, an honourary professor at Rikkyo 
University, said the recent search was like a rehearsal to 
mobilize the "Self-Defence Forces" in Japan in case a war breaks 
out in the Korean peninsula. He denounced this as an 
unpardonable act to incite the fever of the second Korean war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

