<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Returning Chongnyon Delegation Holds Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Returning Chongnyon Delegation Holds Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0305214094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1503 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0305214094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 1 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- A 
meeting was held in Tokyo on April 28 to hear a report from a 
delegation of veteran officials of the General Association of 
Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) which had visited the 
homeland. 
  Addressing the meeting, the Chief Vice-chairman of the 
Central Standing Committee of Chongnyon, Ho Chong-man, said what 
the members of the large delegation of veteran officials of 
Chongnyon deeply felt again while staying in the homeland was 
that they have the illustrious leader in the person of dear 
Comrade Kim Chong-il who is best in ideology, leadership and 
love for the revolutionary comrades and the people. 
  He said the veteran officials should play a big role in 
strengthening and developing Chongnyon through generations into 
an organization intensely loyal to the illustrious leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il and encouraging and inspiring the Chongnyon 
officials and Koreans in Japan in the patriotic struggle to 
firmly defend the socialist homeland and Chongnyon organisation 
and glorify them. 
  He appealed to all the officials and compatriots to make 
greater efforts for a bigger stride forward in the patriotic 
work of Chongnyon with optimism and firm faith that they will 
unfailingly win when there is supreme commander Comrade Kim 
Chong-il for them. 
  A letter to the dear leader Marshal Kim Chong-il was adopted 
at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

