<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Works Reported by Foreign Media </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Works Reported by Foreign Media </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0505045594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0430 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0505045594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song's famous works "Answers to the Questions 
Raised by the U.S. WASHINGTON TIMES News Coverage Group," 
"Answers to the Questions Raised by the U.S. CNN News Coverage 
Group" and "Answers to the Questions Raised by the Japanese NHK 
News Coverage Group" were reported by foreign news media. 
  The works were reported by the Yugoslav paper POLITIKA with 
a 
portrait of President Kim Il-song under the title "President Kim 
Il- song: We Have No Nuclear Weapons" and by the Vietnamese TV 
with a picture of President Kim Il-song receiving foreign 
delegations. 
  The Danish papers BERLINGSKE TIDENDE and JYLLANDS-POSTEN 
reported that President Kim Il-song said the Korean people love 
peace and set great store by the edifices they have built by 
their devoted efforts. 
  The works were also reported under the titles "President Kim 
Il-song Declares Peace Is the Basic Policy and Fundamental Idea 
of the Workers' Party and Government of Korea," "President Kim 
Il-song Declares the DPRK Has No Nuclear Weapons", etc. By the 
Danish paper POLITIKEN, the Hungarian papers MAGYAR HIRLAP and 
NEPSZABADSAG, the Malaysian paper SIN CHEW JIT POH, the Egyptian 
papers EGYPTIAN GAZETTE, AL AKHBAR and AL AHRAM, the Pakistani 
paper MUSLIM, the Tunisian paper LE RENOUVEAU, the Swiss paper 
RENOUVEAU COTIDIEN, the Chinese paper HEILONGJIANG DAILY, the 
Swedish papers DAGENS NYHETER and SYDSVENSKA DAGBLADET, the 
Jordanian papers AL RAI and AL DUSTOUR, the Kazakh paper VESNIK 
KAZAKHSTANA, Hungarian Radio and TV, Egyptian Central TV and 
Radio Jordan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

