<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Birthday Commemorative Event Ends </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Birthday Commemorative Event Ends </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405062094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0517 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405062094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- Mangyongdae prize sports 
contest which opened on April 4 closed. 
  The traditional sports contest is held every year on the 
occasion of the birthday of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song. 
  Sportsmen of many sports groups participated in more than 50 
events of the sports contest. 
  Four sportsmen set new world records in 6 events. 
  In weightlifting, the last world records were broken by Kim 
Yong-nam with a lift of 203 kg in jerk for the men's 76 g 
category, Yi Song-hui with a total lift of 155 kilograms (68.5 
kg in snatch 87.5 kg in jerk) in the women's 46 kg category, Han 
Kyong-sil with a lift of 70 kg in snatch for the women's 46kg 
category. 
  Kim Il-sin set a new world record in the men's 3000 metres 
of 
short-track speed skating, and six sportsmen improved Asian 
records in four events of weightlifing and speed skating. 
  58 new republican records were set by 48 sportsmen in 49 
events. [sentence as received] 

</TEXT>

