<F P=101> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rice Transplanting Begins in Countryside </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rice Transplanting Begins in Countryside </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0505054194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0446 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0505054194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- Rice-transplanting has 
begun in the countryside of Korea. 
  Co-operative farmers have brought up sturdy rice seedlings 
despite the unfavorable weather in spring this year. 
  They do farming on a scientific and technical basis as 
required by the chuche method. This year, too, they have 
started rice-transplanting when the right time came. 
  Rice-transplanting, one of the most important farming 
processes, begins in early May and is carried out in 20 odd days 
by intensive efforts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

