<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Red Cross Societies Observed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of Red Cross Societies Observed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0505053994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0444 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0505053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held and a 
photo exhibition opened in Pyongyang Wednesday to celebrate the 
75th anniversary of the founding of the League of Red Cross and 
Red Crescent Societies under the sponsorship of the Red Cross 
Society of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  Yi Song-ho, acting chairman of the Central Committee of the 
Red Cross Society of the DPRK, made a report at the meeting. 
  The reporter outlined the significance of the founding of 
the 
league and reviewed the achievements in its activities. 
  He elaborated on major tasks facing the Red Cross Society of 
the DPRK at the present juncture and on the work the society 
must carry out in accordance with the strategy of Red Cross 
development in the 1990s and the 1994-1995 working plan of the 
league. 
  Then, central and local Red Cross officials and voluntary 
servants took the floor. 
  On display at the exhibition were pictures and materials 
showing the relief and community health and public service 
activities of the league and first-aid and other primary medical 
service and prevention of natural disasters, environmental 
protection and other activities of the Red Cross Society of the 
DPRK. 
  The participants saw the exhibits. 
  They planted memorial trees on the anniversary. 
  The Red Cross Society of the DPRK issued postage stamps 
commemorating the anniversary. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

