<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party, Government Officials Watch `Masterpiece' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Party, Government Officials Watch `Masterpiece' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0505054594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0449 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0505054594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- Party and government 
officials saw the 18th part of the multi-part feature film "The 
Nation and Destiny" on May 4. 
  The film was seen by Choe Kwang, Kye Ung-tae, Han Song-yong 
and other senior party and government officials. 
  "The Nation and Destiny" Part 18 which was completed as a 
masterpiece under the guidance of the party deals with the life 
of the heroine Ho Chong-sun who covered an eventful road because 
she failed to meet a wise leader after setting out on the 
communist movement in the 1920s for the independence of Korea. 
  The film deeply anatomizes the tragic communist movement in 
those days when it was divided into various factions by their 
disgusting fighting and vividly proves the truth that only when 
the whole nation is united around the wise leader, guided by 
him, is it possible to restore the lost country and win victory 
in revolution. 

</TEXT>

