<H3> <TI>   Prasong Discusses Safety Zone in Cambodia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prasong Discusses Safety Zone in Cambodia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0505015094 Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 in Thai 
1200 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0505015094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today Foreign Minister Squadron Leader Prasong 
Sunsiri received Rupert Von Arney, visiting representative of 
the UN High Commissioner for Refugees [UNHCR]. They discussed 
the refugee situation in Thailand. The UNHCR representative 
expressed satisfaction with the Thai Government's care of the 
refugees. At the meeting, the foreign minister suggested that 
the UN establish an area in Cambodia to receive refugees fleeing 
from the fighting. The UNHCR representative accepted the 
suggestion for consideration. 
  [Begin recording] [Suwit Simasakun, Foreign Ministry 
Information Department director, in progress] ...replied that it 
may be possible to implement the idea. However, it depends on 
the political situation in Cambodia. This is because neither 
Khmer side would want the other to have access to its 
population. In any event, the UNHCR representative accepted the 
idea for consideration. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

