<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Committee Reviews Proposed Laws </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Committee Reviews Proposed Laws </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0305111894 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 1 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0305111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Assembly Judiciary Committee held a 
conference in Hue from 25 to 30 April to review a number of 
proposed laws and decrees to be presented for the National 
Assembly Standing Committee's consideration and approval. 
Attending the conference were representatives of the government 
Cadre Organization Committee, the party Central Committee 
Organization and Internal Affairs Departments, the National 
Assembly Economic and Budget Committee, the National Assembly 
Secretariat, and the People's Council and other agencies of Thua 
Thien-Hue Province. 
  The conference heard reports on the bills amending and 
supplementing the Law on the People's Council and People's 
Committee; the Law on the Election of People's Councillors; the 
law regarding the rights and obligations of organizations at 
home in using land allocated or leased to them by the state; and 
the law regarding the rights and obligations of foreign 
organizations and individuals who are granted land leases in 
Vietnam. The conference also reviewed the Civil Servant Code 
and heard a report from the chief judge of the Supreme People's 
Court on the court's working mechanism. 
  During their discussion, members of the National Assembly 
Judiciary Committee contributed many ideas to help the concerned 
agencies revise and perfect these drafts of laws and decrees, 
which will eventually contribute to the reconstruction of our 
nation.. 

</TEXT>

