<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Convicted Japanese Journalist Deported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Convicted Japanese Journalist Deported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405124194 Seoul YONHAP in English 1133 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 4 (YONHAP) -- The Japanese Fuji-TV Seoul 
bureau chief, who has been sentenced to a suspended prison term 
for violating the military secret protection law, was deported 
from Korea on last April 28, a Justice Ministry official said 
Wednesday. 
  The Japanese journalist, Masatoshi Sinohara, has drawn two 
years in prison with a stay of execution for three years. The 
appellate court verdict was confirmed as he did not appeal. 
  "Under the immigration law, those foreigners sentenced to 
prison terms are supposed to be deported. We have also banned 
him from visiting Korea for the next five years," the Ministry 
official said. 

</TEXT>

